  <prompt>
    Implement `POST /api/insights/ask` Minimal API endpoint per SPEC §3.1 D-P15. Accepts `{question, subject, parameters}`, returns InsightArtifact or DeclineResponse via `IInsightsAi.AnswerQuestionAsync` facade. Endpoint filter for resource auth (ADR-008); rate limiting (ADR-016); ProblemDetails errors (ADR-019). Zone B — calls facade only; §3.5 forbidden imports verified by grep.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer with Minimal API + ADR-008 endpoint filter + ADR-016 rate limiting + ADR-019 ProblemDetails expertise.</role>

  <goal>
    Endpoint registered in EndpointMappingExtensions.cs as `MapInsightsAskEndpoint()`. POST with valid {question, subject, parameters} returns 200 with InsightArtifact OR 200 with DeclineResponse (per facade response shape). Invalid request returns 400 + ProblemDetails. Unauthenticated returns 401; unauthorized returns 403. Rate-limited returns 429. Integration test against fixture invokes end-to-end via mocked IInsightsAi.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r1/SPEC.md (§3.1 D-P15, §3.5 facade boundary, §5.1.1 acceptance)</file>
    <file purpose="claude">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r1/CLAUDE.md (forbidden imports in Zone B)</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Endpoint filter for resource auth — verify caller has tenant access</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-016">Rate limiting per caller (default 60 requests/minute)</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">ProblemDetails for all errors with appropriate problem type URIs</constraint>
    <constraint source="§3.5">Zone B placement (Api/Insights/); MUST inject IInsightsAi only; NO IChatClient / PlaybookExecutionEngine imports</constraint>
    <constraint source="D-27">DefaultAzureCredential for Dataverse outbound (if endpoint reads access scope from Dataverse)</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>minimal-api, endpoint-filter, rate-limiting, problemdetails, facade-consumption</topic>
    <files>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-008-endpoint-filter-authorization.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-016-ai-cost-rate-limit-and-backpressure.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-019-problemdetails.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Author InsightAskRequest DTO">In Models/Insights/ — {Question, Subject, Parameters} with validation attributes</step>
    <step order="2" name="Author endpoint">Api/Insights/InsightEndpoints.cs with MapInsightsAskEndpoint(); POST /api/insights/ask handler</step>
    <step order="3" name="Endpoint filter">Tenant access verification per ADR-008</step>
    <step order="4" name="Rate limit">Per-caller bucket via existing rate limiting middleware (ADR-016)</step>
    <step order="5" name="Inject IInsightsAi">Call IInsightsAi.AnswerQuestionAsync(request, ct) → return result.Artifact OR result.Decline</step>
    <step order="6" name="ProblemDetails">Validation failure → 400 ProblemDetails; auth failure → 401/403 ProblemDetails; rate limit → 429 ProblemDetails</step>
    <step order="7" name="Register in DI">EndpointMappingExtensions.cs adds MapInsightsAskEndpoint() call</step>
    <step order="8" name="Integration test">POST valid request → expect 200 + InsightArtifact; POST invalid → 400; mock IInsightsAi for sufficient + insufficient paths</step>
    <step order="9" name="§3.5 grep">Run boundary verification on Api/Insights/ → zero hits expected</step>
    <step order="10" name="Quality gates">code-review + adr-check</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build and test</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Insights/InsightEndpoints.cs</output>
